.TH PROMETHEUS\-FAIL2BAN\-EXPORTER 1 "2023-12" "0.10.1" Prometheus
.SH NAME
prometheus\-fail2ban\-exporter \- fail2ban Prometheus exporter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B prometheus-fail2ban-exporter
.RI [ option ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
NGINX Prometheus exporter makes it possible to monitor fail2ban process
using Prometheus.
.PP
\f[B]fail2ban\f[] exposes a handful of metrics via the socket. 
\f[B]fail2ban Prometheus exporter\f[] fetches the metrics from a single
fail2ban server (socket), converts the metrics into appropriate 
\f[B]Prometheus\f[] metrics types and finally exposes them via an HTTP 
server to be collected by Prometheus.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \--dry-run
Attempt to connect to the fail2ban socket then exit before starting 
the server.
.TP
.BR \--web.listen-address " \fIstring\fP"
An address or unix domain socket path to listen on for web interface and
telemetry. The default value can be overwritten by LISTEN_ADDRESS
environment variable. (default ":9191").
.TP
.BR \--web.basic-auth.username "\ \fIstring\fP"
Username to use to protect endpoints with basic auth
.TP
.BR \--web.basic-auth.password " \fIstring\fP"
Password to use to protect endpoints with basic auth
.TP
.BR \--collector.f2b.socket " \fIstring\fP"
Path to the fail2ban server socket (default: /var/run/fail2ban/fail2ban.sock)
.TP
.BR \--collector.f2b.exit-on-socket-connection-error
When set to true the exporter will immediately exit on a fail2ban socket 
connection error
.TP
.BR \--collector.textfile.directory " \fIstring\fP"
Directory to read text files with metrics from
.SH SEE ALSO
\f[B]fail2ban\f[](8), \f[B]prometheus\f[](1)
.SH AUTHOR
Hector

